race.comment: AZABELLE (2) led and just missed over 1675m at Bunbury last time out when on the quick turnaround. She'll carry less weight today and steps up in trip for just the second time. Rates highly on her last start effort and can go one better this time around. ANTZ PANTZ BABY (7) jumps right out in trip now, though she should have a solid enough fitness base to do so. She closed off nicely over 1400m at Bunbury last time out and the inside draw should see her get every chance in running. Looks set for a bold run getting out to a more suitable trip today. OISIN (1) beat home AZABELLE last start and meets that galloper worse at the weights this time around. He'll be on speed again from the draw which is always a positive however, and if he can dictate the speed then he'll be tough to reel in. ELEGANT INDI (5) was solid last start in tougher grade after a good win fresh. Big chance with Pike reuniting. ANNIE WARBUCKS (6) has to be included following a nice last start effort.
